---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Beacon Local builds websites and manages SEO for pelvic floor physical therapy practices — so the patients searching for help can find the providers who can give it."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'About', url: '/about/' }]}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-28 pb-16 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img src={`${base}images/hero-lighthouse.jpg`} alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-brand-dark/70"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-max relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <span class="section-label text-brand-accent">About</span>
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-white">Why Beacon Local Exists</h1>
        <p class="section-description text-white/80">
          People are searching for help with things they've been told are just normal. The practice that can help them should be the one they find.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story Section -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="container-max">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-brand-dark-light text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Somewhere right now, someone is searching for help with pelvic floor issues they’ve been told are just normal — leaking after childbirth, pain they’ve been told to live with, questions they’ve been dismissed about for years. Someone else is pregnant and trying to prepare their body for birth, and not sure where to start. They’re all ready to do something about it. They just need to find the right provider.
          </p>
          <p>
            That provider might be you. But if your practice isn’t showing up when they search, they’ll never know.
          </p>
          <p>
            I started building websites and doing SEO for pelvic floor PT practices after working with one and seeing exactly that gap. The practice was doing genuinely important work — and trying to build an online presence with a self-built Wix site and limited visibility into what actually makes a difference in search. Meanwhile, the cheapest outside help she’d found started at $800 a month and didn’t cover half of what was needed.
          </p>
          <p>
            That’s why Beacon Local exists. The independent PT who went into this field to help people shouldn’t have to become a marketing expert to reach them.
          </p>

          <!-- Philosophy Box -->
          <div class="bg-surface-alt p-6 rounded-lg my-8 border-l-4 border-brand-primary">
            <h3 class="text-base mb-2 text-brand-primary-dark font-heading font-semibold">How we work</h3>
            <p class="mb-2">
              We do honest SEO. No tricks, no shortcuts that look good for a month and then backfire. We won’t stuff keywords into your Google Business Profile name or build spammy links. We help you show up for the searches that matter, consistently, because the work is done right.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Fair value matters to us. Our pricing reflects doing the work well, not charging what we can get away with. You should always be getting more out of this than you’re putting in.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p>
            We got into this because we believe the patients searching for help should be able to find the people who can give it. That’s what we’re here for.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-padding pt-0">
    <div class="container-max">
      <div class="cta-section max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl">Let's Get Your Practice Found</h3>
        <p class="text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">
          If any of this sounds familiar, we'd love to hear about your practice.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="https://calendar.app.google/CMRnDVxeQcVm6Mgm9" class="btn btn-primary bg-brand-accent border-brand-accent hover:bg-brand-accent-dark hover:border-brand-accent-dark">
            Get in Touch
          </a>
          <a href={`${base}services/`} class="btn bg-transparent text-white border-white hover:bg-white hover:text-brand-primary">
            View Services
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
